com.noctarius.tengi.serialization.marshaller

Interface Marshaller<O>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    MarshallerReader<O>, MarshallerWriter<O>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    DebuggableMarshaller<O>

    public interface Marshaller<O>
extends MarshallerReader<O>, MarshallerWriter<O>
    The Marshaller interface defines a type to be used to create external serialization mechanisms based on an acceptance criteria (e.g. a special super-type or an annotation).

      • marshaller

        static <O,I> Marshaller<O> marshaller(I marshallerId,
                                      MarshallerReader<O> reader,
                                      MarshallerWriter<O> writer)
        This method is a convenience way to build a Marshaller instance from two lambdas. It will wrapped the given two functions into a new Marshaller instance.
        Parameters:
        marshallerId - the protocol id of the marshaller
        reader - the marshall logic implementation (or function)
        writer - the un-marshall logic implementation (or function)
        Returns:
        a wrapper Marshaller instance
